586
00:19:59,740 --> 00:20:00,920
Yummy.

587
00:20:02,099 --> 00:20:02,779
Slow down, slow down.

588
00:20:04,099 --> 00:20:06,619
I'm an expert at taking care of the elderly.

589
00:20:07,099 --> 00:20:07,900
Back in the day,

590
00:20:08,539 --> 00:20:11,279
I took care of Dabao's grandpa.

591
00:20:11,700 --> 00:20:12,500
Dad.

592
00:20:12,819 --> 00:20:14,759
If the pressure is too hard or soft,

593
00:20:14,940 --> 00:20:16,240
just say the word.

594
00:20:16,339 --> 00:20:16,980
Good.

595
00:20:16,980 --> 00:20:18,140
Just right.

596
00:20:20,339 --> 00:20:22,380
I married into your family at twenty-one.

597
00:20:23,299 --> 00:20:25,420
Working and raising Bao'er.

598
00:20:25,980 --> 00:20:28,339
Massaging shoulders, washing feet.

599
00:20:28,700 --> 00:20:30,740
With elders above and little ones below.

600
00:20:31,220 --> 00:20:33,299
The kid's dad left early.

601
00:20:33,859 --> 00:20:36,980
Leaving us widow and orphan, and I haven't remarried.

602
00:20:37,220 --> 00:20:38,019
Left...

603
00:20:39,619 --> 00:20:40,259
Didn't go far.

604
00:20:40,259 --> 00:20:41,460
He came back again.

605
00:20:41,460 --> 00:20:43,660
Gotta come home often, right?

606
00:20:44,140 --> 00:20:45,099
He has to help you...

607
00:20:45,480 --> 00:20:46,579
wash the chopsticks,

608
00:20:46,579 --> 00:20:47,500
wash the dishes.

609
00:20:48,420 --> 00:20:50,339
Pound the back, massage the shoulders.

610
00:20:51,039 --> 00:20:52,539
That's great.

611
00:20:53,099 --> 00:20:54,220
Goushengzi.

612
00:20:55,220 --> 00:20:56,299
I'm calling you, Goushengzi.

613
00:20:58,259 --> 00:20:58,859
Look.

614
00:20:58,859 --> 00:21:00,460
Look how good your wife is.

615
00:21:00,460 --> 00:21:00,940
Good.

616
00:21:02,180 --> 00:21:02,980
Come here.

617
00:21:03,220 --> 00:21:04,859
Massage Dad's legs.

618
00:21:04,859 --> 00:21:05,460
Hurry.

619
00:21:05,460 --> 00:21:06,220
Massage legs.

620
00:21:07,099 --> 00:21:08,140
Kneel down. Massage legs.

621
00:21:17,140 --> 00:21:17,819
Dad

622
00:21:18,740 --> 00:21:21,180
Can't you let someone else push for a while?

623
00:21:21,700 --> 00:21:24,059
I've been pushing you for ages.

624
00:21:24,900 --> 00:21:26,059
If I didn't have a son,

625
00:21:26,460 --> 00:21:27,539
I'd let someone else.

626
00:21:28,140 --> 00:21:30,460
With a son here, why ask someone else?

627
00:21:31,140 --> 00:21:32,380
Hurry up.

628
00:21:32,619 --> 00:21:33,619
Push me.

629
00:21:33,740 --> 00:21:35,859
Go around the lake three more times.

630
00:21:40,539 --> 00:21:41,619
This is killing me.

631
00:21:42,779 --> 00:21:44,740
I wasn't this tired even in the Army Corps.

632
00:21:45,940 --> 00:21:47,339
Gou'er Ye's ancestors

633
00:21:47,579 --> 00:21:49,180
must have been local tyrants or bullies.

634
00:21:49,259 --> 00:21:51,299
How can he be so good at torturing people?

635
00:21:51,819 --> 00:21:52,799
If this keeps up,

636
00:21:53,859 --> 00:21:54,940
Gou'er Ye, the white-haired one,

637
00:21:54,940 --> 00:21:56,519
is bound to bury me, the black-haired one.

638
00:21:56,940 --> 00:21:57,740
Lao Li,

639
00:21:57,740 --> 00:21:59,980
take a look at yourself in your phone camera.

640
00:21:59,980 --> 00:22:01,279
Do you even have any hair left?

641
00:22:01,579 --> 00:22:03,339
You really think you're thirty-three?

642
00:22:04,380 --> 00:22:05,900
Actually, compared to Gou'er Ye,

643
00:22:05,900 --> 00:22:07,059
we aren't that much younger.

644
00:22:09,380 --> 00:22:10,900
Student Wang Song is right.

645
00:22:11,660 --> 00:22:12,380
People...

646
00:22:12,940 --> 00:22:14,380
everyone gets old eventually.

647
00:22:14,740 --> 00:22:16,299
And that day

648
00:22:16,779 --> 00:22:17,859
isn't far off.

649
00:22:19,660 --> 00:22:21,420
As for the next Alzheimer's case,

650
00:22:21,420 --> 00:22:22,539
who knows who it'll be?

651
00:22:23,059 --> 00:22:23,859
If it's me,

652
00:22:25,019 --> 00:22:26,339
you all have to humor me too.

653
00:22:27,779 --> 00:22:28,579
Xiao Fan,

654
00:22:29,539 --> 00:22:30,619
you pretend to be my son.

655
00:22:32,140 --> 00:22:33,880
Why should you be the one with Alzheimer's?

656
00:22:34,259 --> 00:22:35,539
As if no one else can get it.

657
00:22:35,539 --> 00:22:37,339
Right, maybe I'll get it before you guys.

658
00:22:38,579 --> 00:22:39,980
Is this really something to compete over?

659
00:22:46,460 --> 00:22:47,859
Professor Fan is here.

660
00:22:47,859 --> 00:22:48,819
It's me, Gou'er Ye.

661
00:22:49,740 --> 00:22:50,819
Mr. Liu.

662
00:22:50,859 --> 00:22:51,779
Yes, it's me.

663
00:22:52,900 --> 00:22:54,700
Gou'er Ye's confusion has passed.

664
00:22:55,099 --> 00:22:56,700
Look at me, who am I?

665
00:22:56,700 --> 00:22:58,140
Brother Lao Liang.

666
00:22:59,619 --> 00:23:01,059
Sister Xiao Cai.

667
00:23:02,619 --> 00:23:03,900
I was confused just now.

668
00:23:03,900 --> 00:23:05,299
I had a dream.

669
00:23:06,180 --> 00:23:07,960
I dreamt you were pretending to be my son,

670
00:23:07,960 --> 00:23:09,059
pretending to be my daughter-in-law.

671
00:23:09,779 --> 00:23:10,579
It was so funny.

672
00:23:11,819 --> 00:23:12,619
Really?

673
00:23:13,059 --> 00:23:14,140
Gou'er Ye isn't confused anymore.

674
00:23:14,140 --> 00:23:14,640
Yes.

675
00:23:14,819 --> 00:23:16,099
I'm not confused.

676
00:23:16,660 --> 00:23:17,460
Son,

677
00:23:18,819 --> 00:23:20,579
old landlord Qi Yongnian's family...

678
00:23:20,579 --> 00:23:22,259
those few acres of prime land at the big diagonal corner,

679
00:23:22,259 --> 00:23:24,180
did you buy them for me?

680
00:23:24,980 --> 00:23:26,900
Well, he still doesn't get it.

681
00:23:33,420 --> 00:23:35,019
My poor old back

682
00:23:37,019 --> 00:23:38,740
Go ask for that wheelchair

683
00:23:39,220 --> 00:23:40,140
I need to use it

684
00:23:41,140 --> 00:23:43,299
It's been less than two days and I can't take it

685
00:23:44,059 --> 00:23:45,559
Let whoever wants to handle it do it

686
00:23:46,500 --> 00:23:47,539
I'm done

687
00:23:48,660 --> 00:23:49,819
Gou'er Ye is a sick man

688
00:23:50,140 --> 00:23:51,380
You have to bear with him

689
00:23:52,099 --> 00:23:53,500
At our age

690
00:23:54,500 --> 00:23:55,779
who isn't sick?

691
00:23:56,779 --> 00:23:58,460
Does being sick give you the right to bully people?

692
00:23:59,579 --> 00:24:00,940
Gou'er Ye, you're here

693
00:24:00,940 --> 00:24:01,700
Grandpa Gou'er

694
00:24:02,180 --> 00:24:02,980
No need

695
00:24:03,940 --> 00:24:04,740
Dad

696
00:24:06,819 --> 00:24:08,000
Who are you calling Dad?

697
00:24:09,660 --> 00:24:11,099
Who is your dad?

698
00:24:11,099 --> 00:24:11,779
No

699
00:24:11,859 --> 00:24:13,420
He's really sick

700
00:24:14,859 --> 00:24:15,220
This...

701
00:24:17,500 --> 00:24:18,539
No need

702
00:24:18,680 --> 00:24:19,140
No need

703
00:24:19,359 --> 00:24:19,819
No need

704
00:24:20,299 --> 00:24:21,640
Gou'er Ye has come to his senses

705
00:24:21,819 --> 00:24:23,220
Lao Li, you're liberated

706
00:24:23,460 --> 00:24:24,059
Just like that

707
00:24:27,099 --> 00:24:29,299
severed the father-son relationship so quickly?

708
00:24:30,140 --> 00:24:32,160
Suddenly having no one to wait on

709
00:24:32,740 --> 00:24:34,519
feels a bit empty inside

710
00:24:39,220 --> 00:24:39,900
President Li

711
00:24:39,900 --> 00:24:41,839
You've recovered quite well

712
00:24:42,619 --> 00:24:44,099
My back is fine now

713
00:24:44,740 --> 00:24:46,740
but my memory is getting worse and worse

714
00:24:47,380 --> 00:24:49,180
I remember I had something to do today

715
00:24:49,180 --> 00:24:50,819
but I just can't recall what it was

716
00:24:51,460 --> 00:24:52,259
Say

717
00:24:53,539 --> 00:24:54,980
this Alzheimer's

718
00:24:55,140 --> 00:24:56,660
is it contagious?

719
00:24:56,819 --> 00:24:58,619
Your memory is fine

720
00:24:59,619 --> 00:25:00,420
Mr. Liu

721
00:25:00,619 --> 00:25:01,420
President Li

722
00:25:01,619 --> 00:25:03,539
If I get confused one day

723
00:25:04,180 --> 00:25:05,200
and call you my husband

724
00:25:05,400 --> 00:25:06,380
please don't get angry

725
00:25:07,400 --> 00:25:08,019
Okay

726
00:25:09,059 --> 00:25:10,799
You have to play along and humor me too

727
00:25:11,259 --> 00:25:11,980
You...

728
00:25:11,980 --> 00:25:13,099
Say, Lao Li

729
00:25:13,259 --> 00:25:15,660
didn't we agree to meet at Yongfeng Mall?

730
00:25:15,660 --> 00:25:16,779
Why didn't you go?

731
00:25:16,779 --> 00:25:18,380
Made me wait there like a fool for half an hour

732
00:25:18,380 --> 00:25:19,740
That's the thing! I forgot

733
00:25:19,740 --> 00:25:20,660
Look at my memory

734
00:25:21,779 --> 00:25:22,980
You took care of Gou'er Ye for a few days

735
00:25:22,980 --> 00:25:24,420
and now you've got senile dementia too?

736
00:25:24,420 --> 00:25:25,380
I really might have a bit

737
00:25:27,500 --> 00:25:28,740
Then the 30,000 yuan you owe

738
00:25:28,740 --> 00:25:29,660
don't forget to pay me back

739
00:25:29,660 --> 00:25:30,380
Nonsense

740
00:25:30,980 --> 00:25:32,420
When did I ever borrow money from you?

741
00:25:33,059 --> 00:25:34,579
If anything, you've taken advantage of me plenty

742
00:25:35,500 --> 00:25:36,299
Tuesday

743
00:25:36,900 --> 00:25:37,700
we took a taxi together

744
00:25:37,700 --> 00:25:38,539
I paid the fare

745
00:25:39,339 --> 00:25:40,380
The fifth of last month

746
00:25:40,460 --> 00:25:41,819
you had a toothache and I bought the medicine

747
00:25:42,099 --> 00:25:43,220
I didn't ask you to reimburse me, did I?

748
00:25:43,380 --> 00:25:43,839
And also

749
00:25:43,839 --> 00:25:45,299
the second day I arrived at the community

750
00:25:45,299 --> 00:25:46,339
you used my shaver

751
00:25:46,339 --> 00:25:47,140
and you broke it

752
00:25:47,140 --> 00:25:47,980
Don't listen to his nonsense

753
00:25:47,980 --> 00:25:48,720
That never happened

754
00:25:48,819 --> 00:25:50,140
You still haven't paid me back for it

755
00:25:50,140 --> 00:25:51,180
Pay me for my shaver

756
00:25:51,460 --> 00:25:52,420
With a memory like that

757
00:25:52,700 --> 00:25:54,380
you won't get Alzheimer's

758
00:25:55,180 --> 00:25:55,980
Sister

759
00:25:55,980 --> 00:25:57,119
Goodbye

760
00:25:58,259 --> 00:25:59,359
What are we practicing today?
